short.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G: Converts Unix timestamps to human-readable dates

long.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G:
Convert timestamps inline - no need to copy and paste the numbers, read the dates in their places so that you can follow along whatever you were trying to read.

Convert ALL timestamps at once (in an instant) - if you are looking at a bunch of events that happen, ALL of their dates will be converted immediately

Convert them back - if you want to see the original unix timestamp format, just convert them back.

If you are just debugging logs and you find a bunch of unix timestamps, just click to read those dates, if you speak human of course.
